<subSubSection box="[199,1431,649,674]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,613,1142]" box="[199,1431,649,674]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,316,649,674]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Tegmen with large, round ivory spot near base of costa (
<figureCitation box="[913,989,649,674]" captionStart="FIGURE 34 – 36" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1630,1652]" captionTargetBox="[232,1357,202,1599]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[217,1369,195,1606]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 34 – 36. Facial aspect (34), lateral aspect (35), tegmen in widest aspect (36) of Lepyronoxia. A, O. irregularis sp. nov.; B, O. frontalis (Stål); C, O. boliviana sp. nov.; D, O. obliqua (Jacobi), male; E, O. quadrimaculata (Lallemand); F, O. rana (Walker); G, O. decorata sp. nov.; H, O. oculata sp. nov.; J, O. sphaerata sp. nov.; K, O. subfasciata (A. &amp; S.); L, O. obscurata (A. &amp; S.), male; M, O. bufo (Walker). Scale line: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217121/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">
Fig. 
<number box="[961,989,649,674]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" value="35.0">35</number>
</figureCitation>
H); thecal tip diamond-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[1323,1399,649,674]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 17" captionStartId="5.[151,264,918,941]" captionTargetBox="[217,1363,209,878]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[217,1369,195,894]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 17. Male theca of Orthorapha s. s. (3 – 5), subgenus Balsania (6 – 7) and Lepyronoxia (8 – 17), lateral (A) and caudal aspect of tip (B): 3, O. cassidioides; 4, O. laeta; 5, O. invidia; 6, O. reducta; 7, O. sagittata; 8, O. obscurata; 9, O. inscripta; 10, O. decorata; 11, O. oculata; 12, O. bufo; 13, O. rana (type of O. glabrata); 14, O. subfasciata; 15, O. frontalis; 16, O. quadrimaculata; 17, O. sphaerata. Scale line: 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217116/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">
Fig. 
<number box="[1372,1399,650,674]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
B).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="222" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,613,1142]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,685,710]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Description.</emphasis>
Tan to sordid greenish with face and costal margins of tegmina dark brown to black, with round ivory spot near base of costa larger than yellow to ivory spots on midlength and near apex of costa and another on apex of central discal cell (
<figureCitation box="[456,539,757,782]" captionStart="FIGURE 34 – 36" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1630,1652]" captionTargetBox="[232,1357,202,1599]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[217,1369,195,1606]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 34 – 36. Facial aspect (34), lateral aspect (35), tegmen in widest aspect (36) of Lepyronoxia. A, O. irregularis sp. nov.; B, O. frontalis (Stål); C, O. boliviana sp. nov.; D, O. obliqua (Jacobi), male; E, O. quadrimaculata (Lallemand); F, O. rana (Walker); G, O. decorata sp. nov.; H, O. oculata sp. nov.; J, O. sphaerata sp. nov.; K, O. subfasciata (A. &amp; S.); L, O. obscurata (A. &amp; S.), male; M, O. bufo (Walker). Scale line: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217121/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">
Fig. 
<number box="[509,539,757,782]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" value="35.0">35</number>
</figureCitation>
H); pale lines on crown (as in 
<taxonomicName box="[880,1015,757,781]" class="Insecta" family="Aphrophoridae" genus="Orthorapha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decorata">
<emphasis box="[880,1015,757,781]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">O. decorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) weakly marked; irregular pale spots also on sides of pronotum; veins on tegminal tips pale. Head well produced, as long as median length of pronotum; frons inflated, rounded in dorsal aspect, receding in profile; crown declivous; frons scarcely lower than clypellus at maximum expansion; head as wide as pronotum; lateral margins of pronotum much shorter than eye; tegmina densely covered with small pits, twice as long as broad, with veins weakly carinate; hind wings as in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Aphrophoridae" genus="Orthorapha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="concinna">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Orthorapha concinna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[268,334,937,962]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1584,1606]" captionTargetBox="[276,1312,273,1556]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[265,1321,267,1560]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. New World Orthoraphini: habitus (A – B), hind wing (C – F) including detail of hamuli on costal margin (G – H), male abdomen in ventral aspect (J) and male genital capsule in lateral aspect (K). A, Orthorapha (Lepyronoxia) frontalis (Stål); B, F, H, O. cassidioides Westwood, female; C, Orthorapha (Lepyronoxia) obliqua (Jacobi); D, Orthorapha (Balsania) concinna (Stål); E, G, Orthorapha (Balsania) geminata (Jacobi); J, K, Orthorapha (Lepyronoxia) bufo (Walker)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217115/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">
Fig. 
<number box="[320,334,938,962]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
D) but with apical cell shorter, crossvein r-m situated more distad as in 
<taxonomicName box="[1126,1245,937,961]" class="Insecta" family="Aphrophoridae" genus="Lepyronia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obliqua">
<emphasis box="[1126,1245,937,961]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">O. obliqua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1260,1327,937,962]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1584,1606]" captionTargetBox="[276,1312,273,1556]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[265,1321,267,1560]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. New World Orthoraphini: habitus (A – B), hind wing (C – F) including detail of hamuli on costal margin (G – H), male abdomen in ventral aspect (J) and male genital capsule in lateral aspect (K). A, Orthorapha (Lepyronoxia) frontalis (Stål); B, F, H, O. cassidioides Westwood, female; C, Orthorapha (Lepyronoxia) obliqua (Jacobi); D, Orthorapha (Balsania) concinna (Stål); E, G, Orthorapha (Balsania) geminata (Jacobi); J, K, Orthorapha (Lepyronoxia) bufo (Walker)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217115/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">
Fig. 
<number box="[1312,1327,938,962]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
C). Theca shaft sinuate in lateral aspect, in caudal aspect strongly broadened and with angular processes at midlength, tip spatulate, membranous, with broad gonopore (
<figureCitation box="[691,773,1009,1034]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 17" captionStartId="5.[151,264,918,941]" captionTargetBox="[217,1363,209,878]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[217,1369,195,894]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 17. Male theca of Orthorapha s. s. (3 – 5), subgenus Balsania (6 – 7) and Lepyronoxia (8 – 17), lateral (A) and caudal aspect of tip (B): 3, O. cassidioides; 4, O. laeta; 5, O. invidia; 6, O. reducta; 7, O. sagittata; 8, O. obscurata; 9, O. inscripta; 10, O. decorata; 11, O. oculata; 12, O. bufo; 13, O. rana (type of O. glabrata); 14, O. subfasciata; 15, O. frontalis; 16, O. quadrimaculata; 17, O. sphaerata. Scale line: 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217116/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">
Fig. 
<number box="[747,773,1010,1034]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
A–B). Length: male 6.0– 
<quantity box="[1066,1157,1009,1034]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.9" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" unit="mm" value="6.9">6.9 mm</quantity>
, female 
<quantity box="[1259,1352,1010,1034]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.4" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" unit="mm" value="7.4">7.4 mm</quantity>
. Width across head or pronotum: male 
<quantity box="[503,591,1046,1070]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" unit="mm" value="2.4">2.4 mm</quantity>
, female 
<quantity box="[686,775,1046,1070]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" unit="mm" value="2.7">2.7 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
