</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[562,645,1397,1422]" captionStart="FIGURE 34 – 36" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1630,1652]" captionTargetBox="[232,1357,202,1599]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[217,1369,195,1606]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 34 – 36. Facial aspect (34), lateral aspect (35), tegmen in widest aspect (36) of Lepyronoxia. A, O. irregularis sp. nov.; B, O. frontalis (Stål); C, O. boliviana sp. nov.; D, O. obliqua (Jacobi), male; E, O. quadrimaculata (Lallemand); F, O. rana (Walker); G, O. decorata sp. nov.; H, O. oculata sp. nov.; J, O. sphaerata sp. nov.; K, O. subfasciata (A. &amp; S.); L, O. obscurata (A. &amp; S.), male; M, O. bufo (Walker). Scale line: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217121/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">
Fig. 
<number box="[616,645,1397,1422]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" value="35.0">35</number>
</figureCitation>
H), but with large costal pale spot irregular in shape, broad wing tips without pale preapical spots, and theca with digitate tip contrasting strongly with lamellate shaft (
<figureCitation box="[1242,1324,1433,1458]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 17" captionStartId="5.[151,264,918,941]" captionTargetBox="[217,1363,209,878]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[217,1369,195,894]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 17. Male theca of Orthorapha s. s. (3 – 5), subgenus Balsania (6 – 7) and Lepyronoxia (8 – 17), lateral (A) and caudal aspect of tip (B): 3, O. cassidioides; 4, O. laeta; 5, O. invidia; 6, O. reducta; 7, O. sagittata; 8, O. obscurata; 9, O. inscripta; 10, O. decorata; 11, O. oculata; 12, O. bufo; 13, O. rana (type of O. glabrata); 14, O. subfasciata; 15, O. frontalis; 16, O. quadrimaculata; 17, O. sphaerata. Scale line: 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217116/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">
